{"timestamp": "2025-12-03 17:42:51.413612", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission recorded.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"load_balancer\", \"server_access_router\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"host_incorrect_ip\", \"ospf_area_misconfiguration\"]\n\nRecommended next steps (optional, not submitted):\n- Confirm intended backend subnet (20.200.0.0/24) vs actual (10.200.0.0/24) and correct the load_balancer eth1 IP or move backends to the intended subnet.\n- Remove/stop advertising the backend server network into OSPF on server_access_router (or implement proper VLAN isolation / ACLs) so backend servers are not directly reachable from user nets.\n- Verify FRR/OSPF configs on server_access_router and core to ensure only intended networks are advertised.\n- Test connectivity after changes: ensure hosts can reach load_balancer VIP but not backend IPs; ensure LB can reach backends via the backend-only interface.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2870, "output_tokens": 199, "total_tokens": 3069, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2688}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
